#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:0.5"
msgid "53. Hasadhammasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.53\">Monks’ Confession 53: the training rule on "
"playing</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.112
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.53.1\">Bu-Pc.53.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\""
" id=\"BD.2.390\">BD.2.390</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1038</a>On one occasion, "
"while the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū aciravatiyā nadiyā udake "
"kīḷanti."
msgstr ""
"the monks from the group of seventeen <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.112\""
">Vin.4.112</a> were playing in the water in the river Aciravatī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo mallikāya deviyā saddhiṃ "
"uparipāsādavaragato hoti."
msgstr ""
"Just then King Pasenadi of Kosala was up in his best stilt house with queen "
"Mallikā"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.4"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho rājā pasenadi kosalo sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū aciravatiyā nadiyā "
"udake kīḷante."
msgstr "and he saw the monks from the group of seventeen playing in the river."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.5"
msgid "Disvāna mallikaṃ deviṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He said to queen Mallikā,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.6"
msgid "“ete te, mallike, arahanto udake kīḷantī”ti."
msgstr "“Mallikā, these perfected ones are playing in the water.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.7"
msgid "“Nissaṃsayaṃ kho, mahārāja, bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ apaññattaṃ."
msgstr "<p>“Great King, no doubt the Master hasn’t laid down a rule."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.8"
msgid "Te vā bhikkhū appakataññuno”ti."
msgstr "Either that, or these monks are ignorant of the rules.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho rañño pasenadissa kosalassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "<p>King Pasenadi thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.10"
msgid ""
"“kena nu kho ahaṃ upāyena bhagavato ca na āroceyyaṃ, bhagavā ca jāneyya ime "
"bhikkhū udake kīḷitā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“How can the Master find out about these monks playing in the water without "
"me telling him?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū pakkosāpetvā mahantaṃ "
"guḷapiṇḍaṃ adāsi—"
msgstr ""
"<p>King Pasenadi then summoned those monks and gave them a large lump of "
"sugar, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.12"
msgid "“imaṃ, bhante, guḷapiṇḍaṃ bhagavato dethā”ti."
msgstr "“Venerables, please give this lump of sugar to the Master.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.13"
msgid ""
"Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū taṃ guḷapiṇḍaṃ ādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "<p>The monks took the lump of sugar and went to the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.14"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "They said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.15"
msgid "“imaṃ, bhante, guḷapiṇḍaṃ rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavato detī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, this lump of sugar is a gift from King Pasenadi.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.16"
msgid "“Kahaṃ pana tumhe, bhikkhave, rājā addasā”ti."
msgstr "<p>“But, monks, where did you see the king?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.17"
msgid "“Aciravatiyā nadiyā, bhagavā, udake kīḷante”ti."
msgstr ""
"p><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.391\">BD.2.391</a>“From the river "
"Aciravatī, while we were playing in the water.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.18"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "<p>The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.19"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, udake kīḷissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you play in water?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.20"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.21"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: hasadhamme → hassadhamme (bj, s1-3) | hāsadhamme (pts1)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:1.22"
msgid "“Udake hasadhamme pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1039</a>‘If a monk plays in water, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.1.1"
msgid "Udake hasadhammo nāma"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.53.2\"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-"
"Pc.53.2.1\">Bu-Pc.53.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1040</a><term>Plays in "
"water</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.1.2"
msgid ""
"uparigopphake udake hasādhippāyo nimujjati vā ummujjati vā palavati vā, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if, aiming to have fun, he immerses himself or emerges on the surface "
"or swims, in water which is more than ankle deep, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.1"
msgid "Udake hasadhamme hasadhammasaññī, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.52.2.2\">Bu-Pc.52.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1041</a>If he is playing in water, and he perceives that he is, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.2"
msgid "Udake hasadhamme vematiko, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is playing in water, but he is unsure if he is, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.3"
msgid "Udake hasadhamme ahasadhammasaññī, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is playing in water, but he does not perceive that he is, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.4"
msgid "Heṭṭhāgopphake udake kīḷati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1042</a>If he is playing in water less than ankle "
"deep, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.5"
msgid "Udake nāvāya kīḷati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"rule\">If he is playing with a boat in water, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct.</span>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.6"
msgid ""
"Hatthena vā pādena vā kaṭṭhena vā kaṭhalāya vā udakaṃ paharati, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"rule\">If he strikes the water with his hand, with his foot, "
"with a stick, or with a stone, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</span>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.7"
msgid ""
"Bhājanagataṃ udakaṃ vā kañjikaṃ vā khīraṃ vā takkaṃ vā rajanaṃ vā passāvaṃ "
"vā cikkhallaṃ vā kīḷati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"rule\">If he plays with water, conjee, milk, buttermilk, dye, "
"urine, or mud, in a container, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct.</span></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.8"
msgid "Udake ahasadhamme hasadhammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1043</a>If he is not playing in water, but he "
"perceives that he is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.9"
msgid "Udake ahasadhamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is not playing in water, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense "
"of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.2.10"
msgid "Udake ahasadhamme ahasadhammasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If he is not playing in water, and he does not perceive that he is, there is "
"no offense.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7, pts-vp-pli4.113
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.53.2.3\">Bu-Pc.53.2.3</a><a class=\"pts-vp-"
"en\" id=\"BD.2.392\">BD.2.392</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1044</a>There is no "
"offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"na hasādhippāyo, sati karaṇīye udakaṃ otaritvā nimujjati vā ummujjati vā "
"palavati vā, pāraṃ gacchanto nimujjati vā ummujjati vā palavati vā, āpadāsu, "
"ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he is not aiming to have fun; if, when there is a need, he enters the "
"water <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.113\">Vin.4.113</a> and then "
"immerses himself or emerges on the surface or swims; if, while crossing a "
"body of water, he immerses himself or emerges on the surface or swims; if "
"there are dangers; if he is insane; if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc53:2.3.3"
msgid "Hasadhammasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1045</a>The third rule, the "
"training rule on playing, is finished.</p>"
